messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full HTTP request path:
  /admin/printshops

- All HTTP methods acceptable:
  false

- Per-method acceptance (based on the code in AdminController.getPrinShopsList):
  - HEAD: false
  - POST: false
  - OPTIONS: false
  - TRACE: false
  - GET: true
  - PUT: false
  - DELETE: false
  - PATCH: false

Explanation:
- The method is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/admin/printshops", method = RequestMethod.GET). That explicitly maps the endpoint to the path "/admin/printshops" and only the GET HTTP method.
- There is no class-level @RequestMapping that would add a prefix; the controller only has @RestController and @Transactional, so the full path is exactly the value in the method-level mapping.
- Because the mapping explicitly restricts to RequestMethod.GET, "all methods" is false.
- The code does not declare HEAD/OPTIONS/TRACE/POST/PUT/DELETE/PATCH for this path. Although many HTTP servers/frameworks auto-handle HEAD or OPTIONS when GET is present, the task required judging acceptability based on the code (annotations) only, so those methods are marked false.
- The method is also @Secured({"ROLE_ADMIN"}) which affects authorization but does not change which HTTP methods are mapped.
